## Summary

Add `v-else` and `v-else-if` directive support to the template compiler.

Currently only `v-if` is supported. `v-else` and `v-else-if` are explicitly rejected in `builder_validate.mbt`.

## Expected behavior

```html
<template>
  <div v-if='count > 0'>positive</div>
  <div v-else-if='count == 0'>zero</div>
  <div v-else>negative</div>
</template>
```

Should generate conditional branching in both client and server codegen.

## Notes

- Requires sibling element tracking in the template builder
- Must validate that `v-else`/`v-else-if` follows a `v-if` or `v-else-if` sibling